`viz/` is a single-file browser tool with no build step and only one
artifact: `index.html`. It has no internal structure to coordinate — the
directory boundary exists purely to isolate this standalone consumer from
the Rust compiler it visualizes.

Its contract with the rest of the codebase is read-only and via JSON:
it consumes `../out/viz-data.json` (produced elsewhere by a `viz-data`
binary) and duplicates, rather than imports, two pieces of Rust logic that
must be watched for drift — `parse_stroke`/bank-order constants from
`crates/steno/src/stroke/keys.rs`, and the snippet-escaping scheme from
`crates/steno/src/snippet/mod.rs`. Any change to either of those Rust
modules requires a matching manual edit here or the tool silently
misrenders (wrong keyboard highlights, stray backslashes) while still
running without error.

No intent.md exists for this directory.